name: CathyMcMorrisRodgers
tweet_text: As our friend Frank Stephens would say, Cole‚Äôs life is worth living. Today, he‚Äôs almost 13 years old. He's smart & loves sports. He‚Äôs a great big brother to our daughters Grace & Brynn. All five of us just skied down Mt. Spokane this weekend. It was a joy for the entire family.

name: CathyMcMorrisRodgers
tweet_text: But Cole‚Äôs life couldn‚Äôt be further from what we were told. He‚Äôs opened our eyes to the dignity and potential of every life. He‚Äôs reminded me that just because challenges in life are hard, it doesn‚Äôt mean they aren‚Äôt valuable.

name: CathyMcMorrisRodgers
tweet_text:
Doctors gave us a long list of challenges and complications. We were told don‚Äôt expect much. In that moment, I could see how the fear of the unknown could make us question everything. 

Could we give Cole everything that life had to offer? Could we handle this?

name: CathyMcMorrisRodgers
tweet_text: I think back to the uncertainty, the fear. Even when I was pregnant it was scary, especially the first time! My oldest Cole was born with Down syndrome. It wasn‚Äôt what Brian or I hoped for or dreamed.

name: CathyMcMorrisRodgers
tweet_text: That changed in my first term when I met Brian. We got married and became pregnant shortly after. Three kids later, I can testify today that becoming a mom has been the best thing to have happened in my life. The absolute best thing.

name: CathyMcMorrisRodgers
tweet_text:
Every woman‚Äôs journey to motherhood is different. Something that unites us though is the uncertainty and fear of the unknown.

For me, I was 35 and single when I was elected to Congress. I wasn‚Äôt sure about having kids. Was I a baby person? Would it ever happen for me?
